# CODEOWNERS template for spec-driven repos
#
# This is a TEMPLATE, not an active CODEOWNERS file. Copy this into
# .github/CODEOWNERS in your OWN repo and replace the @your-* placeholder
# team handles with real GitHub teams or users.
#
# Paired with the `spec-driven` preset and the `OpenSpec Validate` CI gate,
# this gives you per-capability review routing: every PR that touches a
# given capability's spec automatically requires a review from that
# capability's owner.
#
# GitHub docs: https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/managing-your-repositories-settings-and-security/customizing-your-repository/about-code-owners

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------
# Capability-level ownership
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------
# Canonical post-ship specs — authoritative contract per subsystem.
# Anyone changing a capability's spec requires the owner's approval.

# openspec/specs/auth/               @your-auth-team
# openspec/specs/billing/            @your-platform-team
# openspec/specs/checkout/           @your-commerce-team
# openspec/specs/observability/      @your-sre-team
# openspec/specs/incident-analysis/  @your-sre-team

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------
# In-flight changes (openspec/changes/)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------
# Each active change folder can have its own ownership. Useful for
# routing PRs that modify an in-progress spec to the right reviewer.
# By default, any touch of openspec/changes/ requires the platform/arch
# team to review the shape.

# openspec/changes/                  @your-platform-team

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------
# Plugin / config surfaces
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------
# Changes to the routing config, hooks, or presets affect every
# developer's workflow — require platform review.

# config/                            @your-platform-team
# hooks/                             @your-platform-team
# .github/workflows/                 @your-platform-team

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------
# Catch-all (optional)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------
# Fallback owner for anything not matched above. Comment out if you
# prefer no fallback (unmatched files require no review).

# *                                  @your-default-team
